@endnode
@node INTRO "Why did I do it"

    Being Webmaster for our Club, and being mandated to send
    every month notices for our meetings, I was finding awkward
    to have to use an ARexx script with @{b}"YAM"@{ub}.

    Also, I wanted to send each message individually as to make
    sure no one would get the addresses of the other recepients
    (and mostly of our members).

    I then decided to take out my C manuals and my SAS/C development
    kit, and I got to work.

    The first problem was to build the interface.  I used the
    @{b}gtlayout@{ub} library, which has enormously simplified
    things for me.

    Then, I had to figure out a way to send @{b}ARexx@{ub} messages to
    @{b}YAM@{ub}, because the @{b}ARexx@{ub} documentation that was available to
    me was not too helpful in that context.

    In short, after a few days of programming , there it is:
    @{FG shine}YAM2MM@{FG text}

@endnode
@node REQ "Requirements"

    · An Amiga with OS 2.04 and up ...

    · YAM :o), by Marcel Beck, with the ARexx interface

    · gtlayout.library, by Olaf `Olsen' Barthel

    · Also, you want to make sure that "rexxsyslib.library"
      is in your LIBS: directory, and that "RexxMast" has
      been launched. These two files come with OS 2.04 and up.

@endnode
