@endnode
@node INSTALL "Comment installer"

    1. Copy @{FG shine}YAM2MM@{FG text} anywhere you want (the YAM: directory is
       a good idea...)

    2. Install gtlayout.library in your LIBS: directory

    3. You must create a text file containing all the e-mail
       addresses (one per line) of the people to which you want
       to send messages.  A standard text editeur (i.e. Ed,
       GoldED, CygnusED, etc.) will do the job.

    4. Then, it's time to configure @{b}YAM@{ub}.

       In @{u}'Settings/Configuration/Arexx'@{uu}:

       · Select one of the menu entries @{u}("'Scripts' menu entry...")@{uu}.

       · Under @{u}'Name'@{uu}, put the name of the menu item that you
         want (i.e "YAM2MM", "Mail Merge", "Family matters",
         etc.).

       · Select the @{u}'AmigaDOS'@{uu} option of the "cycle gadget".

       · Under @{u}'Script'@{uu}, put "YAM2MM" (with path) and the
         options.

       · @{b}** CAUTION **@{ub} Do not check the @{u}'Wait for termination'@{uu} option.

       · Save the new configuration.

    Et voilŕ !

@endnode
@node OPTIONS "A few particularities"


    P=PATH/K,SUB=SUBJECT/K,L=LIST/K,PUB=PUBSCREEN/K,NI=NOICONIFY/S:


    PATH        The path or text file that will serve as content
                for the message. By default the program will use
                @{u}SYS:@{uu} if nothing is specified.

    SUBJECT     The default subject for the message.

    LIST        The file (with path) containing the list of
                e-mail addresses. By default the program will use
                @{u}PROGDIR:mm.list@{uu} if nothing is specified.

                Caution if you launch @{FG shine}YAM2MM@{FG text} as a script from
                YAM, the PROGDIR: in this case will be the directory
                containing YAM.

    PUBSCREEN   The public screen where @{FG shine}YAM2MM@{FG text} will open is
                the @{u}WorkBench@{uu} by default.

    NOICONIFY   By default @{FG shine}YAM2MM@{FG text} iconify YAM to generate its
                messages, which speed up things considerably.
                This parameter will deselect that function in
                order to examine in detail the proceedings.

@endnode
@node USAGE "Usage"

    Here in a few words is the description of the interface and
    of the gadgets and their particularities.

    The top part of the screen is filled by a 'listview' that
    shows the content of the address list. This list is made
    up of a text file that the user can specify at the launch
    of the program using the @{u}LIST@{uu} parameter.

    Clicking on one of the line in the 'listview' will display
    it in the space right below the 'listview'.  It is possible
    to temporarily remove this entry from the list with the
    "@{FG shine}Remove Name@{FG text}" button.

    The "@{FG shine}Change List@{FG text}" button calls up an ASL requester that
    enable you to load a new list into the 'listview'.

    The "@{FG shine}Subject :@{FG text}" input string contains the subject of the
    messages to send.  The user can define it when launching
    the program with the @{u}SUBJECT@{uu} parameter.

    The "@{FG shine}Message :@{FG text}" input string contains the name of the
    text file (with path) that will serve as content for the
    messages to send.  The user can define it when launching
    the program with the @{u}PATH@{uu} parameter.

    By default @{FG shine}YAM2MM@{FG text} iconify YAM to generate its messages,
    which speed up things considerably. The @{FG shine}"Iconify YAM"@{FG text}
    checkbox will select or deselect that function.

    The "@{FG shine}Send@{FG text}" button will send all the necessary informations
    to YAM's ARexx interface in order to generate the messages.

    Finally, the "@{FG shine}Status@{FG text}" textbox display messages on the
    proceedings.


@endnode
@node FUTURE "Future"

    As is, this program seems to brilliantly fill its purpose, but
    if you think that some improvement could be made, I would be
    glad to hear about them and (maybe) add them to a future
    version of @{FG shine}YAM2MM@{FG text}.

    You can drop me a note by @{"e-mail" link AUT} to let me know.

@endnode
